```python
import pandas as pd

def read_excel(filepath):
    return pd.read_excel(filepath)

# Example usage:
data = read_excel('example.xlsx')
print(data)
```
This function uses the Pandas library to read an Excel spreadsheet and returns a DataFrame containing the data from the spreadsheet. You can replace `'example.xlsx'` with the path to your own Excel file.
